casebody.data:
Gray, Appellant, v. Tompkins, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. January 4, 1892.) Action by William Gray against Calvin Tompkins. Motion to strike cause from calendar. Judgment of affirmance.

Argued before Bookstaver, Bischoff. and Pryor, JJ.

Warner & Frayer, for appellant. W. J. Lardner, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion denied, without costs. See 15 N. Y. Supp. 953.
